obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42843)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42843&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Land Improvement Loans Act,`
  line 1883.
  line
  line `(2) Local extent. Commencement.--It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the`
  line `territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B`
  line `States], but shall not come into force in any part of ^2`
  line `[the territories to which this Act`
  line `extends] until such date as the State Government ^3*** may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Extension of Acts no. XIX of 1883 and No. XII of 1884 to Hyderabad and`
  line `Saurashtra area of the State of Bombay.--The Land Improvement Loan Act, 1883 and`
  line `the Agriculturists' Loans Act, 1884, (XIX of 1883), are hereby extended to and shall be,`
  line `in virtue of such extension, in force in the Hyderabad and Saurashtra area of the State of`
  line Bombay.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1958, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Consequential and other amendments to Act XIX of 1883.--In section 1, to`
  line `sub-section (2) the following proviso shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that on the commencement of the Land Improvement Loans and`
  line `Agriculturists' Loans (Extension and Amendment) Act, 1957, this Act shall also`
  line `extend to and be in force in, the Hyderabad and Saurashtra areas of the state of`
  line `Bombay."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay act XXVII of 1958, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "a Part A State or a Part C State ".`
  line
  line `3. The words "with the previous sanction of the G.G. in C," rep. by Act 8 of 1906, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42844)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Acts 26 of 1871 and 21 of 1876 repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42844&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Land Improvement Act, 1871,`
  line `and Act XXI of 1876 (An Act to amend the Land Improvement Act, 1871), shall, except as`
  line `regards the recovery of advances made before this Act comes into force and costs`
  line `incurred by the Government in respect of such advances, be r epealed.`
  line
  line `(2) When in any Act, Regulation or Notification passed or issued before this Act`
  line `comes into force, reference is made to either of those Acts, the reference shall, so far`
  line `as may be practicable, be read as applying to this Act or the corresponding p art of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42845)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `“Collector” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Cf. the definition in s. 3 (10) of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42845&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "Collector"`
  line `^1means the Collector of land-revenue`
  line `of a district, or the Deputy Commissioner, or any officer empowered by the State`
  line `Government by name or by virtue of his office to discharge the functions of a Collector`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42846)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Purposes for which loans may be granted under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words "with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." omitted by Act 8 of 1906, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42846&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such`
  line `rules as may be made under section 10, loans may be granted under this Act, by such`
  line `officer as may, from time to time, be empowered in this behalf by the State Government,`
  line `for the purpose of making any improvement, to any person having a right to make that`
  line `improvement, or, with the consent of that person, to any other person.`
  line
  line `(2) "Improvement" means any work which adds to the letting value of land, and includes the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the construction of wells, tanks and other works for the storage, supply or`
  line `distribution of water for the purposes of agriculture, or for the use of men and cattle`
  line `employed in agriculture;`
  line
  line `(b) the preparation of land for irrigation;`
  line
  line `(c) the drainage, reclamation from rivers or other waters, or protection from floods or`
  line `from erosion or other damage by water, of land used for agricultural purposes or wasteland`
  line `which is culturable;`
  line
  line `(d) the reclamation, clearance, enclosure or permanent improvement of land for`
  line `agricultural purposes;`
  line
  line `(e) the renewal or reconstruction of any of the foregoing works, or alterations therein or`
  line `additions thereto; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other works as the State Government ^1*** may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be improvements for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `In section 4, in sub-section (2), for the words "any work which adds to the letting value of`
  line `land" the words "in relation, to any land, any work which adds to the value of the land and`
  line `which is suitable thereto as also consistent with the purpose for which it is held" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1958, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42847)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Mode of dealing with applications for loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42847&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application for a loan is`
  line `made under this Act, the officer to whom the application is made may, if it is, in his`
  line `opinion, expedient that public notice be given of the application, publish a notice, in such`
  line `manner as the State Government may, from time to time, direct, calling upon all persons`
  line `objecting to the loan to appear before him at a time and place fixed therein and submit their`
  line objections.
  line
  line `(2) The officer shall consider every objection submitted under sub-section (1), and make an`
  line `order in writing either admitting or overruling it:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when the question raised by an objection is, in the opinion of the officer,`
  line `one of such a nature that it cannot be satisfactorily decided except by a Civil Court, he`
  line `shall postpone his proceedings on the application until the question has been so decided.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42848)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Period for repayment of loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42848&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every loan granted under this Act shall be`
  line `repayable by instalments (in the form of an annuity or otherwise), within such period from the`
  line `date of the actual advance of the loan, or, when the loan is advanced in instalments, ^1[from the`
  line `date of the advance of the last instalment actually paid] as may, from time to time, be fixed by`
  line `the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The period fixed as aforesaid shall not ordinarily exceed thirty-five years.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government ^2***, in making ^3*** the rules fixing the period, shall, in`
  line `considering whether the period should extend to thirty-five years, or whether it should extend`
  line `beyond thirty-five years, have regard to the durability of the work for the purpose of which the`
  line `loan is granted, and to the expediency of the cost of the work being paid by the generation of`
  line `persons who will immediately benefit by the work.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1899, s. 2, for "from the date of the actual advance of the last instalment".`
  line
  line `2. The words "and G. G. in C." omitted by Act 8 of 1906, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. The words "and sanctioning" omitted by s. 3. ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42849)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Recovery of loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42849&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may be made under section 10, all loans`
  line `granted under this Act, all interest (if any) chargeable thereon, and costs (if any) incurred in`
  line `making the same, shall, when they become due, be recoverable by the Collector in all or any of the`
  line `following modes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) from the borrower--as if they were arrears of land-revenue due by him;`
  line
  line `(b) from his surety (if any)--as if they were arrears of land-revenue due by him;`
  line
  line `(c) out of the land for the benefit of which the loan has been granted--as if they were`
  line `arrears of land-revenue due in respect of that land;`
  line
  line `(d) out of the property comprised in the collateral security (if any)--according to the`
  line `procedure for the realization of land-revenue by the sale of immovable property other than the`
  line `land on which that revenue is due:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceeding in respect of any land under clause (c) shall affect any`
  line `interest in that land which existed before the date of the order granting the loan, other than`
  line `the interest of the borrower, and of mortgagees of, or persons having charges on, that`
  line `interest, and, where the loan is granted under section 4 with the consent of another person,`
  line `the interest of that person, and of mortgagees of, or persons having charges on, that`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) When any sum due on account of any such loan, interest or costs is paid to the`
  line `Collector by a surety or an owner of property comprised in any collateral security, or is`
  line `recovered under sub-section (1) by the Collector from a surety or out of any such property,`
  line `the Collector shall, on the application of the surety or the owner of that property (as the case`
  line `may be), recover that sum on his behalf from the borrower, or out of the land for the benefit`
  line `of which the loan has been granted, in manner provided by sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be in the discretion of a Collector acting under this section to determine the order`
  line `in which he will resort to the various modes of recovery permitted by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42850)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Order granting loan conclusive on certain points.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42850&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A written order under the hand`
  line `of an officer empowered to make loans under this Act granting a loan to, or with the consent`
  line `of, a person mentioned therein, for the purpose of carrying out a work described therein, for`
  line `the benefit of land specified therein, shall, for the purposes of this Act, be conclusive`
  line evidence--
  line
  line `(a) that the work described is an improvement within the meaning of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) that the person mentioned had at the date of the order a right to make such an`
  line `improvement; and`
  line
  line `(c) that the improvement is one benefiting the land specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42851)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Liability of joint borrowers as among themselves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42851&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `When a loan is made under this`
  line `Act to the members of a village-community or to any other persons on such terms that all of`
  line `them are jointly and severally bound to the Government for the payment of the whole amount`
  line `payable in respect thereof, and a statement showing the portion of that amount which as`
  line `among themselves each is bound to contribute is entered upon the order granting the loan and`
  line `is signed by each of them and by the officer making the order, that statement shall be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the portion of that amount which as among themselves each of those`
  line `persons is bound to contribute.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42852)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42852&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The State Government ^1*** may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules consistent with this Act to provide for the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of making applications for loans;`
  line
  line `(b) the officers by whom loans may be granted;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of conducting inquiries relative to applications for loans, and the powers`
  line `to be exercised by officers conducting those inquiries;`
  line
  line `(d) the nature of the security to be taken for the due application and repayment of the`
  line `money, the rate of interest at which, and the conditions under which, loans may be granted,`
  line `and the manner and time of granting loans;`
  line
  line `(e) the inspection of works for which loans have been granted;`
  line
  line `(f) the instalments by which, and the mode in which, loans, the interest to be charged on`
  line `them and the costs incurred in the making thereof, shall be paid;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of keeping and auditing the accounts of the expenditure of loans and of the`
  line `payments made in respect of the same; and`
  line
  line `(h) all other matters pertaining to the working of the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.The words "subject to the control of the G.G. in C," omitted by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the`
  line `Schedule, Part I.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42853)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Exemption of improvements from assessment to land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42853&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When land is`
  line `improved with the aid of a loan granted under this Act, the increase in value derived from`
  line `the improvement shall not be taken into account in revising the assessment of land-revenue`
  line `on the land:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows--`
  line
  line `(1) where the improvement consists of the reclamation of wasteland, or of the`
  line `irrigation of land assessed at unirrigated rates, the increase may be so taken into account`
  line `after the expiration of such period as may be fixed by rules to be framed by the State`
  line `Government ^1***;`
  line
  line `(2) nothing in this section shall entitle any person to call in question any assessment of`
  line `land-revenue otherwise than as it might have been called in question if this Act had not been`
  line passed.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42854)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Certain powers of State Government to be exercisable by Board of Revenue or Financial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578&sectionId=42854&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00003_188319_1523272692578
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Certain powers of State Government to be exercisable by Board of Revenue`
  line `or Financial Commissioner.--The powers conferred on a State Government by sections`
  line `4 (1), 5 (1) and 10 may, in a State for which there is a Board of Revenue or a Financial`
  line `Commissioner, be exercised in the like manner and subject to the like conditions by such`
  line `Board or Financial Commissioner, as the case may be: Provided that rules made by a`
  line `Board of Revenue or Financial Commissioner shall be subject to the Control of the State`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 12 ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and Sch., Pt. I. The original s. 12 had been rep. by Act 16 of 1908. The application of`
  line `this section has been barred in U.P. by the U.P. Board of Revenue Act, 1922 (U.P. 12 of 1922).`
